             <span class="fs-5 mb-2">What is Aspergillus lgG</span> 
             <p style="text-align:justify;">The Aspergillus IgG test is a blood test used to detect the presence of Immunoglobulin G (IgG) antibodies specific to Aspergillus, a type of mold commonly found in the environment. The immune system produces IgG antibodies in response to exposure to Aspergillus. This test helps identify whether a person has been exposed to Aspergillus in the past, or if they are suffering from a chronic infection or allergic reaction related to Aspergillus.</p>
             <hr>
             <span class="fs-5 mb-2">What is Aspergillus lgG used for?</span>
             <p>The Aspergillus lgG test is primarily used to</p> 
             <p class="mb-2" style="text-align: justify;">The Aspergillus IgG test is primarily used to diagnose chronic or invasive Aspergillus infections. Aspergillus can cause severe infections, particularly in people with weakened immune systems (such as those undergoing chemotherapy, organ transplants, or individuals with conditions like HIV/AIDS).</p>
             <p class="mb-2" style="text-align: justify;">In people with compromised immunity, Aspergillus can cause aspergillosis, a fungal infection that affects the lungs and other organs. The IgG test helps determine if there has been exposure to Aspergillus, which might indicate an ongoing or previous infection.</p>
             <p class="mb-2" style="text-align: justify;">The test is used to assess past exposure to Aspergillus, even if there is no active infection. Elevated IgG levels can indicate that a person has been exposed to Aspergillus in the past, and their immune system has produced antibodies as a result.</p>
             <p class="mb-2" style="text-align: justify;">It is particularly useful for individuals who live or work in environments where Aspergillus exposure is common, such as in damp buildings, construction sites, or areas with poor ventilation.</p>
            
